WEBVTT

00:00.626 --> 00:02.586
EPISODE 48
EXECUTION

00:02.670 --> 00:04.505
[water running]

00:56.015 --> 00:58.392
[muffled garbling]

01:13.741 --> 01:15.701
♪

01:48.275 --> 01:50.569
[garbling]

01:50.611 --> 01:52.446
[footsteps]

02:10.965 --> 02:13.050
[garbling]

02:39.242 --> 02:40.661
[garbling]

02:53.340 --> 02:54.800
[grunting]

03:35.799 --> 03:37.926
[♪ opening theme song playing]

03:37.968 --> 03:41.889
JUJUTSU KAISEN: EXECUTION

04:18.383 --> 04:22.512
CULLING GAME

05:15.983 --> 05:17.901
[MAN] So, tell me,

05:18.819 --> 05:20.528
is Mai dead?

05:20.946 --> 05:22.156
[MAKI'S MOTHER]
It's the clan head

05:22.197 --> 05:23.698
you should be concerned about.

05:23.740 --> 05:26.243
And Maki's the one who's
nearly dead, not Mai.

05:26.285 --> 05:27.661
[MAN] Is that so?

05:27.702 --> 05:29.496
Well, I'm glad to hear it.

05:29.788 --> 05:32.624
Maki's a real beauty,
but she's no good.

05:32.666 --> 05:34.375
She can't support a man.

05:34.584 --> 05:36.837
Any woman who can't walk
humbly behind her man

05:36.878 --> 05:39.256
deserves to be stabbed
in the back and killed.

05:39.298 --> 05:41.591
Now Mai's a great woman
in that regard.

05:41.633 --> 05:43.760
SPECIAL FIRST-GRADE SORCERER
NAOYA ZEN'IN

05:45.095 --> 05:46.972
[NAOYA]
She has the same face

05:47.014 --> 05:48.640
and the same great rack as Maki.

05:48.974 --> 05:50.809
She may put on a brave face,

05:50.851 --> 05:52.978
but she understands her place
as a woman.

05:53.020 --> 05:54.188
[MAN] You're late.

05:54.521 --> 05:56.648
Where were you
and what have you been doing?

05:56.690 --> 05:59.234
Your father is in
critical condition!

05:59.276 --> 06:00.861
[NAOYA] Sorry about that.

06:00.902 --> 06:03.697
But what difference does it make
if I'm here or not?

06:03.989 --> 06:05.573
Either way, I'm gonna be

06:05.615 --> 06:07.701
the next head
of the Zen'in Clan.

06:09.161 --> 06:11.913
All my older brothers
are a bunch of knuckleheads.

06:11.955 --> 06:14.333
And, Uncle,
you're his little brother,

06:14.373 --> 06:16.126
but you haven't got
what it takes.

06:16.168 --> 06:18.377
And your daughters
are out of the question.

06:19.004 --> 06:21.173
And Jinichi, well...

06:22.841 --> 06:24.718
You don't look the part.

06:24.759 --> 06:28.013
If you had Toji's looks,
it would be a different story.

06:28.055 --> 06:30.182
[loud thud]

06:30.974 --> 06:35.187
SPECIAL FIRST-GRADE
SORCERER OGI ZEN'IN

06:35.229 --> 06:38.023
My father's dying,
cut me some slack, would you?

06:38.940 --> 06:40.441
We're all a little on edge.

06:41.109 --> 06:43.778
[OLD MAN] I see
everyone's finally here.

06:45.197 --> 06:47.991
I've been informed
that Naobito Zen'in,

06:48.033 --> 06:49.326
head of the Zen'in Clan,

06:49.368 --> 06:51.828
has unfortunately taken
his last breath.

06:55.374 --> 06:56.958
I am Furudate.

06:57.000 --> 07:00.254
I was entrusted by Naobito
to read his will to you,

07:00.295 --> 07:03.757
his chosen family members,
upon his passing.

07:04.465 --> 07:05.926
Ogi Zen'in,

07:05.967 --> 07:08.511
Jinichi Zen'in,

07:08.553 --> 07:10.471
and Naoya Zen'in.

07:11.265 --> 07:13.975
Since you are all
gathered here today,

07:14.017 --> 07:17.187
I shall begin the reading
immediately.

07:17.229 --> 07:18.479
Unless, of course,

07:18.521 --> 07:21.900
any of you have an objection
to my doing so.

07:28.282 --> 07:29.574
First item,

07:29.616 --> 07:32.827
Naoya Zen'in shall be made
the 27th head

07:32.869 --> 07:34.413
of the Zen'in Clan.

07:34.871 --> 07:38.750
Second item, Naoya shall inherit
all assets and cursed tools

07:38.792 --> 07:41.253
that are currently stored
in either Jujutsu High,

07:41.295 --> 07:44.089
or the Zen'in Clan's
forbidden vaults.

07:45.173 --> 07:46.758
In addition to that,

07:47.008 --> 07:48.509
Naoya shall require agreement

07:48.551 --> 07:51.221
from either Ogi
or Jinichi Zen'in

07:51.263 --> 07:53.390
before making use
of any contents.

07:53.432 --> 07:54.891
[scoffs]

07:55.767 --> 07:57.227
I guess that's fine.

07:57.269 --> 07:58.270
[FURUDATE] However,

07:58.853 --> 08:02.523
in the event that
Satoru Gojo dies before I do,

08:02.565 --> 08:06.069
or otherwise loses the use
of his mental faculties,

08:06.111 --> 08:08.613
then the covenant
with Toji Fushiguro

08:08.655 --> 08:10.115
shall be fulfilled.

08:10.157 --> 08:13.118
Megumi Fushiguro will be
welcomed into the Zen'in Clan,

08:13.160 --> 08:16.121
and that same person
will become...

08:16.371 --> 08:20.541
the new head of the Zen'in Clan,
and inherit its assets.

08:21.835 --> 08:23.795
[NAOYA]
Huh? What the hell?

08:24.254 --> 08:26.214
Those guys have no balls.

08:26.256 --> 08:28.216
They think some
unknown brat as the head

08:28.258 --> 08:29.176
would be better than me,

08:29.217 --> 08:30.885
so they ain't doing jack
about it.

08:32.471 --> 08:35.098
Where's Megumi,
and what is he doing now?

08:35.223 --> 08:36.641
[MAKI'S MOTHER]
I don't know much.

08:36.683 --> 08:39.394
Only that he's on a mission
to find Yuji Itadori

08:39.436 --> 08:40.728
somewhere
in the Tokyo area--

08:40.770 --> 08:42.230
And who's that?

08:42.314 --> 08:44.024
He is the vessel of Sukuna.

08:44.065 --> 08:45.900
[NAOYA]
Then go tell the big shots

08:45.942 --> 08:49.363
that Naoya Zen'in is going
to kill Sukuna's vessel.

08:49.404 --> 08:50.529
[Maki's mother gasps]

08:50.989 --> 08:53.700
[NAOYA] And since Megumi
is with Sukuna's vessel,

08:53.741 --> 08:55.534
I'll kill 'em both together.

08:56.286 --> 08:58.372
Tokyo is in pandemonium
right now.

08:59.289 --> 09:02.583
People can die anytime
for any reason there.

09:02.876 --> 09:06.171
Once I kill him,
the rest will work itself out.

09:09.548 --> 09:11.801
The Zen'in Clan belongs to me!

09:17.891 --> 09:19.476
♪

09:21.311 --> 09:22.479
[Yuji gasps] Die!

09:22.521 --> 09:24.481
- [indistinct shouting]
- [YUJI] Gojo no!

09:24.523 --> 09:26.191
- [NOBARA] Itadori?
- [KENTO] Itadori.

09:26.233 --> 09:27.442
[YUKI] What will you be doing?

09:28.360 --> 09:30.028
♪

09:40.663 --> 09:42.290
[footsteps]

09:53.843 --> 09:55.011
[CHOSO] Yuji.

09:55.845 --> 09:57.472
How are your injuries?

09:58.973 --> 10:01.435
Fine, except for where
I took that Black Flash.

10:01.476 --> 10:03.061
But I'm healing fast.

10:03.978 --> 10:06.189
It's probably because of Sukuna.

10:06.231 --> 10:08.900
I can feel how his power
has grown stronger.

10:10.818 --> 10:13.821
[CHOSO] Yuji,
don't worry about me.

10:13.863 --> 10:15.782
Go back to Jujutsu High.

10:16.450 --> 10:19.744
I'd like to retrieve the remains
of Shoso and the others.

10:21.371 --> 10:22.789
[YUJI] I'm not worried.

10:22.830 --> 10:25.500
It's not an issue of me wanting
to return or not.

10:25.792 --> 10:29.003
Sukuna is plotting something
that uses Fushiguro.

10:29.504 --> 10:32.631
Plus, I've killed
so many people.

10:35.552 --> 10:36.595
[MEGUMI]
How are you going to feel

10:36.635 --> 10:37.720
when someone you save

10:37.762 --> 10:39.889
goes on to kill someone
else later?

10:40.265 --> 10:43.435
[YUJI] I don't think I can stay
with the others anymore.

10:44.811 --> 10:46.062
How do you feel Choso?

10:46.104 --> 10:48.398
You know I killed
your little brothers, too.

10:48.440 --> 10:49.690
[CHOSO] It's fine.

10:49.732 --> 10:51.109
That was an accident.

10:51.485 --> 10:53.403
Eso and Kechizu would have
done the same

10:53.445 --> 10:54.988
if they were in my position.

10:55.029 --> 10:57.031
Forgiving you or not
doesn't matter.

10:57.073 --> 10:59.117
That's what it means
to be siblings.

11:03.622 --> 11:04.705
[YUJI] Let's go.

11:04.998 --> 11:07.542
We need to reduce the number
of cursed spirits.

11:08.793 --> 11:09.877
♪

11:24.309 --> 11:25.519
[Yuji grunts]

11:29.022 --> 11:30.689
[Yuji panting]

11:30.731 --> 11:31.983
♪

11:42.494 --> 11:43.828
[Yuji grunts]

11:49.876 --> 11:51.127
[Yuji grunts]

11:54.631 --> 11:55.590
[grunts]

11:55.632 --> 11:57.509
[cursed spirit groans]

11:59.594 --> 12:00.719
♪

12:18.363 --> 12:19.989
[cursed spirit growls]

12:26.329 --> 12:27.372
[Yuji grunts]

12:29.583 --> 12:32.085
[cursed spirits growling]

12:36.423 --> 12:38.508
[growling continues]

12:38.550 --> 12:39.967
[Yuji panting]

12:59.279 --> 13:00.697
Choso!

13:07.579 --> 13:08.787
I got 'em.

13:21.175 --> 13:22.801
[CHOSO] How terrifying.

13:23.177 --> 13:25.846
I already sensed he was
powerful when we fought.

13:26.431 --> 13:28.767
But now he's added
subtlety to it.

13:29.225 --> 13:32.019
He has unfaltering control
of his cursed energy

13:32.061 --> 13:34.188
and exceptional
physical strength.

13:35.814 --> 13:37.484
He's like a war god!

13:37.816 --> 13:40.819
Crazy that he wasn't
in top shape until now.

13:42.614 --> 13:45.074
You're very impressive,
little brother.

13:45.116 --> 13:46.867
Do you have to keep saying that?

13:47.535 --> 13:49.245
[CHOSO] As often as it takes.

13:49.746 --> 13:52.373
Remember, they should
have been there.

13:55.960 --> 13:58.379
Your father should have
also had stitches

13:58.421 --> 14:00.214
in his forehead, too.

14:01.591 --> 14:03.718
[NAOYA] Don't tell me
Megumi's not here.

14:03.760 --> 14:05.386
Am I the first to arrive?

14:05.428 --> 14:08.348
How's that even possible?
He's way too slow.

14:08.723 --> 14:10.099
[YUJI] Who's this guy?

14:10.141 --> 14:12.226
Why's he looking for Fushiguro?

14:12.352 --> 14:14.437
[NAOYA] What are you doing
out here, anyway?

14:14.479 --> 14:16.481
You don't exactly blend in.

14:16.523 --> 14:17.691
Planning an escape?

14:17.732 --> 14:18.817
[YUJI] Escape?

14:18.857 --> 14:20.443
[NAOYA] What, you don't know?

14:20.485 --> 14:22.362
You've been sentenced to death.

14:22.403 --> 14:25.948
After all, you no longer
have Satoru's protection.

14:26.324 --> 14:28.159
- [Choso growls]
- [Yuji gasps]

14:28.618 --> 14:29.952
[TAKUMA] There are
lots of sorcerers

14:29.994 --> 14:31.870
who have been saved
due to Gojo's influence,

14:31.912 --> 14:33.373
pride, and whims.

14:34.332 --> 14:36.376
[NAOYA]
My business is with Megumi,

14:36.417 --> 14:39.754
so to be blunt, I couldn't
care less if you live or die.

14:39.796 --> 14:43.049
Then again, I don't want you
running around willy-nilly,

14:43.090 --> 14:45.009
so I'm gonna
break your legs for now.

14:45.051 --> 14:47.053
What do you want Fushiguro for?

14:47.094 --> 14:49.347
- [NAOYA] I need him to die.
- [Yuji grunts]

14:49.389 --> 14:51.558
[NAOYA] But it'd be great
if he could sign some papers

14:51.599 --> 14:52.767
before he goes.

14:52.933 --> 14:55.311
By the way,
I heard he's looking for you.

14:56.270 --> 14:57.731
[Yuji grunts]

15:01.442 --> 15:02.485
[Choso grunting]

15:16.374 --> 15:19.586
He's certainly faster than us.
But something is off.

15:19.836 --> 15:21.087
Probably his technique.

15:21.128 --> 15:23.381
[NAOYA] You're doing better
than I expected.

15:23.423 --> 15:25.759
I honestly underestimated you.

15:26.217 --> 15:28.511
I know the vessel's
got stuff going on,

15:28.553 --> 15:30.388
but what's that thing
beside him?

15:30.889 --> 15:33.474
Guess I'll crank up
the speed a bit more.

15:35.435 --> 15:36.477
[Yuji gasps]

15:39.021 --> 15:40.939
[YUJI] Am I feeling Gojo?

15:46.529 --> 15:48.865
No, it's even creepier!

15:50.533 --> 15:51.950
Three of you?

15:51.992 --> 15:53.870
I thought you'd be alone.

15:56.080 --> 15:58.875
JUJUTSU KAISEN: EXECUTION

15:59.459 --> 16:00.501
Who is that?

16:01.001 --> 16:02.670
[CHOSO] Whoever he is,
it's bad.

16:03.212 --> 16:05.757
[YUTA] What are your
relationships to Itadori?

16:06.758 --> 16:09.510
[CHOSO] So he's also here
to execute Yuji.

16:17.811 --> 16:20.104
Hold up, pal! I'm on your side.

16:20.521 --> 16:22.857
Your name is Okkotsu, right?

16:22.899 --> 16:24.066
[YUJI] Okkotsu!

16:24.108 --> 16:26.402
The second-year
Fushiguro talked about!

16:26.569 --> 16:28.362
A special-grade sorcerer.

16:28.404 --> 16:29.447
Just like Gojo!

16:29.489 --> 16:30.698
And you are?

16:30.740 --> 16:33.618
I'm Naoya Zen'in.
You know, Maki's cousin.

16:33.660 --> 16:36.245
And I'm here to kill Itadori,
just like you are.

16:36.537 --> 16:38.665
- Yuji, we have to run.
- [NAOYA] So relax.

16:38.706 --> 16:41.083
- [YUJI] Huh?
- I'll stay out of your way.

16:41.125 --> 16:43.711
The blond one's fast
with some kind of trick.

16:43.753 --> 16:46.172
We need to avoid
getting into a chase.

16:46.422 --> 16:47.841
I'll stall, now go!

16:47.882 --> 16:49.216
Will you be okay?

16:49.258 --> 16:51.302
And in return for staying
out of your way

16:51.344 --> 16:52.595
after you kill Itadori,

16:52.637 --> 16:55.055
maybe you could hold off
a bit before reporting it.

16:55.097 --> 16:57.266
I want to use him as bait
for someone else.

16:57.642 --> 16:58.726
I'll be fine.

16:58.768 --> 17:00.728
You're the one
they've come here for.

17:00.770 --> 17:02.062
Not me.

17:02.104 --> 17:05.274
Okkotsu. Just worry about
getting away from him.

17:05.316 --> 17:07.568
He seems like
the same type as Gojo.

17:07.610 --> 17:09.445
You'll die if you fight him.

17:10.488 --> 17:13.031
[NAOYA] I should have
kept quiet about Megumi.

17:13.073 --> 17:14.617
Me and my big mouth.

17:15.033 --> 17:18.078
[CHOSO] My plan keeps Yuji
from fighting another human.

17:18.120 --> 17:20.748
And prevents him from
feeling guilty toward me.

17:20.790 --> 17:23.292
[Choso chuckles]
He's such a handful.

17:23.334 --> 17:25.252
Meet up at
yesterday's spot, Yuji.

17:25.294 --> 17:26.546
Sounds fine.

17:26.587 --> 17:28.381
I'll leave that one
to you, then.

17:28.422 --> 17:29.590
Now!

17:31.759 --> 17:34.721
[YUJI] He's fast!
And with that sword drawn too!

17:36.305 --> 17:37.724
[YUTA] He's pretty quick.

17:37.765 --> 17:39.851
I planned to crush him
when he broke into a run.

17:39.893 --> 17:42.854
[Choso grunts] I was trying
to block Okkotsu's path,

17:42.896 --> 17:44.355
but he read my move!

17:44.522 --> 17:46.649
I was watching you earlier.

17:46.691 --> 17:48.776
That's Blood Manipulation, right?

17:48.985 --> 17:51.612
Only I can't figure out
why you can do it.

17:51.654 --> 17:55.033
Still, it's not that scary,
aside from Piercing Blood.

17:55.073 --> 17:57.869
And producing Piercing Blood
takes Convergence.

17:57.911 --> 17:59.161
There's a long build-up.

17:59.203 --> 18:01.622
I don't think there's
anything left to say.

18:01.664 --> 18:03.917
It's checkmate.
You're going to die.

18:03.958 --> 18:05.793
[CHOSO] You're the one
who will die.

18:05.835 --> 18:08.629
Did you think you could go
after my little brother

18:08.671 --> 18:10.757
and then leave this place alive?

18:14.260 --> 18:16.012
[cursed spirit growls]

18:20.391 --> 18:22.560
[Yuji grunting]

18:22.602 --> 18:23.811
♪

18:24.562 --> 18:25.730
[Yuji grunts]

18:32.570 --> 18:35.573
[YUTA] I'm sure
I was able to cut him.

18:35.615 --> 18:37.324
He's like Maki.

18:53.507 --> 18:54.634
[grunts]

18:58.387 --> 18:59.555
[YUTA] Surprised?

18:59.597 --> 19:02.140
I don't seem like
the power type, do I?

19:02.182 --> 19:04.102
[YUJI] Even without raw power,

19:04.142 --> 19:06.646
he has an insane amount
of cursed energy!

19:06.687 --> 19:08.731
[YUTA] I actually am
on the weaker side.

19:08.773 --> 19:10.608
[YUJI] He's enhancing himself
with cursed energy

19:10.650 --> 19:12.443
to cover for his
lack of strength.

19:12.485 --> 19:14.028
Everyone does that
to some degree,

19:14.070 --> 19:15.153
but when he does it,

19:15.195 --> 19:16.864
it's the exact opposite of me.

19:19.575 --> 19:20.994
Have you noticed?

19:21.035 --> 19:24.038
I have more cursed energy
than your teacher, Gojo.

19:24.080 --> 19:25.081
[Yuji grunts]

19:25.456 --> 19:28.001
[YUTA] However,
Gojo has his Six Eyes.

19:28.042 --> 19:30.461
So he wastes practically
no energy at all

19:30.503 --> 19:32.546
when he activates
his techniques.

19:33.631 --> 19:36.383
He's the best there is
when it comes to performance.

19:36.926 --> 19:40.638
Unlike your teacher,
I can run out of cursed energy.

19:42.015 --> 19:43.766
Enough chit-chat.

19:44.600 --> 19:46.019
♪

19:49.147 --> 19:51.107
- [YUJI] Shit!
- [AOI] The better the sorcerer,

19:51.149 --> 19:52.232
the harder it is to read

19:52.274 --> 19:54.110
the flow of their
cursed energy.

19:54.152 --> 19:55.987
Yours will be hard
to read as well.

19:56.029 --> 19:57.989
[YUJI] That's because
the better the sorcerer,

19:58.031 --> 19:59.573
the more precise
their cursed energy.

20:00.033 --> 20:01.617
That means
you can't predict their attack

20:01.659 --> 20:02.785
until the last second.

20:02.827 --> 20:03.953
[Yuji grunts]

20:04.244 --> 20:05.454
[YUJI] But with this guy,

20:05.496 --> 20:07.289
there's cursed energy
constantly rising

20:07.331 --> 20:08.624
from his entire body.

20:08.666 --> 20:10.001
Even his sword!

20:10.043 --> 20:12.045
It's not even a question
of reading his moves!

20:12.086 --> 20:14.505
He can land decisive blows
with all his attacks.

20:14.547 --> 20:17.257
And he can reduce all damage
to the bare minimum!

20:19.343 --> 20:21.137
[KENTO] You take it from here.

20:21.679 --> 20:23.014
Sorry, Okkotsu,

20:23.056 --> 20:25.474
but I can't afford
to die just yet!

20:33.440 --> 20:35.693
[SATORU] There are some types
who center their training

20:35.735 --> 20:37.444
around the use of a weapon.

20:38.404 --> 20:41.323
But you don't want to become
dependent on a cursed tool

20:41.365 --> 20:43.283
and then neglect...

20:43.325 --> 20:45.703
your manipulation
of cursed energy.

20:45.745 --> 20:49.415
So Slaughter Demon's
just an emergency measure.

20:49.456 --> 20:51.709
[YUJI]
You never taught me this!

20:53.335 --> 20:56.047
You're putting too much focus
into the blade.

20:56.964 --> 20:58.007
[Yuji grunts]

20:58.382 --> 21:00.218
[Yuji grunting, yelling]

21:03.721 --> 21:04.847
[YUTA] It broke?

21:05.305 --> 21:08.434
Of course it did.
He's one of Gojo's students.

21:08.726 --> 21:10.978
I guess you're not going
down easily.

21:11.020 --> 21:12.270
[YUJI] The wound's deep!

21:12.312 --> 21:14.190
But none of my organs
are falling out!

21:14.232 --> 21:15.775
And now we're both
unarmed!

21:15.816 --> 21:17.068
I can win!

21:22.240 --> 21:24.992
[RIKA] What are you two doing?

21:28.162 --> 21:30.790
[YUTA] We're playing, Rika.
That's all.

21:31.665 --> 21:34.127
[YUJI] "Rika"?
What is this thing?

21:34.168 --> 21:37.130
A shikigami?
Where did it come from?

21:38.881 --> 21:40.382
[YUTA] Hold him still.

21:40.424 --> 21:42.218
[Yuji grunts] I can't move!

21:44.762 --> 21:46.388
So strong!

21:53.604 --> 21:55.064
[YUTA] I'm sorry...

22:01.695 --> 22:03.030
Itadori.

22:10.204 --> 22:12.123
[♪ closing theme song playing]

23:40.086 --> 23:41.587
[NAOYA] Older brothers
less competent

23:41.628 --> 23:43.339
than younger brothers
serve no purpose.

23:43.381 --> 23:45.507
[CHOSO] I can't understand how
you never loved your brothers.

23:45.549 --> 23:47.093
[YUTA] Please report
Itadori's death.

23:47.134 --> 23:48.844
[YUKI] That's when
all the distortions started.

23:48.886 --> 23:50.470
[NAOYA]
Don't look down on me!

23:50.512 --> 23:52.390
- [MEGUMI] Start by saving me.
- [CHOSO] This is checkmate.

23:52.430 --> 23:54.767
[MEGUMI] Tsumiki has been
drawn into this game, too.
